author: JEREMY WOZNICK Sports Reporter jwoznick@starherald.com
title: Bearcats to face Gretna in first round of state playoffs
text:
DAVE BRUNZ/Star-Herald Bearcats to face Gretna in first round of state playoffs 
Scottsbluff’s Trevor Garcia runs during a football game against Sidney on Oct. 9. The Bearcats will travel to face Gretna in a first-round playoff game on Friday. Bearcats to face Gretna in first round of state playoffs JEREMY WOZNICK Sports Reporter jwoznick@starherald.com Star Herald Fresh off winning the Class B, District 8 championship for a second consecutive year, the Scottsbluff football team will begin its postseason journey against the Gretna Dragons in a first-round game of the Nebraska state playoffs. The Bearcats, who advanced all the way to the semifinals last year, earned a No. 9 seed in the Class B bracket and will play at No. 8 Gretna on Friday. Kickoff is scheduled for 4 p.m. Both teams enter the contest with 6-3 records.   Remember me on this computer Login   Subscription required
